The paper deals with motion planning, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The use of Gaussian processes and probabilistic inference techniques suggests a strong connection to machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of vision-based perception for motion planning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on continuous-time trajectories suggests a connection to control theory (cs.SY).
